cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the creation of a new corpus of personal stories and their deep representation using Story Intention Graphs. This falls under the domain of natural language processing and computational linguistics, which is covered by the cs.CL sub-category. Additionally, the corpus can be used in applications that involve machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are covered by the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of the corpus in content planning and information retrieval, which are covered by the cs.IR and cs.CY sub-categories, respectively.
